        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1525964158" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18270915037564019112">I want everybody to read, <b>no listen to</b>, The Water is Wide. It is that good a book. There are sublime sentences, most often straight out of the mouths of the eighteen black kids whom he&apos;s teaching, 1969-970, on Yamacraw Island (Daufuski Island), South Carolina. Until he got kicked out for insubordination after one year as a teacher! That is told at the very beginning so it is no spoiler. He is a fantastic teacher. He is the kind of teacher these kids needed. <br/><br/>In the prologue the author says how he</span>
  <span id="freeText18270915037564019112" style="display:none">I want everybody to read, <b>no listen to</b>, The Water is Wide. It is that good a book. There are sublime sentences, most often straight out of the mouths of the eighteen black kids whom he's teaching, 1969-970, on Yamacraw Island (Daufuski Island), South Carolina. Until he got kicked out for insubordination after one year as a teacher! That is told at the very beginning so it is no spoiler. He is a fantastic teacher. He is the kind of teacher these kids needed. <br /><br />In the prologue the author says how he felt the narration of his book by Dan Jon Miller was pure perfection. It captures the essence of his kids' lives. It improves what is at bottom a wonderful book. <br /><br />He tells his story with humor, yet its topic is very serious.</span>
  <a data-text-id="18270915037564019112" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


