<div id="review_2168477630" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2168477630" />
    <a title="Perri" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/17951043-perri"><img alt="Perri" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1362167669p2/17951043.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2168477630?book_show_action=true">Oct 30, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Perri" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Perri" href="/user/show/17951043-perri">Perri</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2168477630" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5633002864010014863">This is not his magnus opus- that would be my just finished Prince of Tides, but I enjoyed this just as much. A young, passionate Conroy has been fired after one year of teaching, then spends time reflecting and writing about his experience. While raging against the racial injustices, he&apos;s candid about his own shortcomings and surprisingly forgiving toward his adversaries. Mostly it&apos;s his love and support of his students which shine the brightest. A great book to end the year, but I think I&apos;ll k</span>
  <span id="freeText5633002864010014863" style="display:none">This is not his magnus opus- that would be my just finished Prince of Tides, but I enjoyed this just as much. A young, passionate Conroy has been fired after one year of teaching, then spends time reflecting and writing about his experience. While raging against the racial injustices, he's candid about his own shortcomings and surprisingly forgiving toward his adversaries. Mostly it's his love and support of his students which shine the brightest. A great book to end the year, but I think I'll keep dipping into the Conrad library in 2018</span>
  <a data-text-id="5633002864010014863" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
